Sentencas: Low temperature solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) has received great interest recently.
Titulo: Effect of MXene on Oxygen Ion Conductivity of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 as Electrolyte for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: However, the low oxygen ion conductivity of electrolyte restricts the operation temperature reduction for SOFC.
Titulo: Effect of MXene on Oxygen Ion Conductivity of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 as Electrolyte for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: In this report, 2D nanomaterial Ti3C2Tx is used as filler doped into the Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) to enhance the conductivity and mechanical strength of composite electrolyte.
Titulo: Effect of MXene on Oxygen Ion Conductivity of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 as Electrolyte for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The 5wt.% Ti3C2Tx/SDC composite membrane exhibits the 3 and 9 times ionic conductivity as that of SDC at 500 degrees C and 600 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Effect of MXene on Oxygen Ion Conductivity of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 as Electrolyte for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: Furthermore, the peak power density of the single cell enhanced by similar to 250% at 500 degrees C.
Titulo: Effect of MXene on Oxygen Ion Conductivity of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 as Electrolyte for Low Temperature SOFC

Sentencas: The addition of Ti3C2Tx-MXene also improved the hardness, fracture toughness and thermal stability of composite membranes.
Titulo: Effect of MXene on Oxygen Ion Conductivity of Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 as Electrolyte for Low Temperature SOFC
